<br>
You can't seriously compare how a law or government policy will affect the populations of two seperate countries.  There are so many different factors that come to play, when you're looking at the impact that such things would have on a society.<br>
<br>
The comparing of such things is just plain ignorance.  Such people are essentially believing that people are people.  A person from England, thinks just like some person from France.  If the events in the last year, havn't woken us up to the fact that people can be very different, we'll forever be left ignorant.<br>
<br>
Think of it this way.  If we took all the criminals from the US prisons, inserted them into a prison in the UK, to carry out the rest of their term.  Do you believe that when they're released into the enlightened United Kingdom, that they'd fly the straight and narrow?<br>
<br>
We're dealing with a different situation in the States, than those in the UK, or any other country.  If we want to have a better understanding of how a law will affect our populace, we'll be looking to compare our different states to each other, rather than looking for comparisions from the outside.<br>
<br>
I certainly don't see any Garden of Eden out there, that's for sure. <p><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6094">Wenin Huirunda</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/udumai01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dumai01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Messiah of the Flameboard</span><br>  Posts: 260<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/7/02 12:18:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=187.topic&index=46>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gun Control and Crime, the English experience</span><hr size=1> &quot;However, afaik, there is almost a one to one correlation between murder rates and legalisation of guns. &quot;<br>
